   391	## 5. Assumptions and the [UNVERIFIED] / uncontrolled register
   392	
   393	Safety-relevant items not yet frozen, and honest control status:
   394	
   395	- **Per-epoch protection-limit numbers** (position/velocity/heading, aided and denied) — the
   396	  baseline gives only campaign-grading acceptance statistics; per-epoch gates are a proposed
   397	  addition.
   398	- **Timers:** `t_lease` (`< 4000 ms`), `t_dr` (DR-authority), per-source freshness deadlines,
   399	  `t_eph` (provisional 6 h), `T_ack`, `caution_enter`/`caution_clear`/`dwell_clear`,
   400	  `dwell_rearm`.
   401	- **G1 arm input:** no arm/disarm message exists in `ARCHITECTURE.md`; an arm-command bus
   402	  message + helm arm input is a contracts requirement per **D13** (U-C1, contracts v3). G1 is
   403	  specified-but-unwired until then.
   404	- **Calibration validity window:** baseline/handoff define no time-based calibration expiry;
   405	  any such window is a **proposed baseline change**, not assumed here (G3 tests presence +
   406	  identity match only).
   407	- **MAVLink revocation command set (Case A):** exact mode-set command, target helm/manual
   408	  mode, RC-arbitration parameters, and the verified ordering (mode-to-manual before nav-injection
   409	  cessation, no actuator discontinuity) — SITL/HIL deliverable on pinned firmware. Until it
   410	  passes, "hand to helm" is unproven.
   411	- **ArduPilot GPS/EKF non-manoeuvre failsafe parameters (Case B):** must prove `GPS_INPUT`
   412	  loss/degradation cannot command RTL/Loiter/disarm; SITL-validated against pinned commit +
   413	  artifact checksum.
   414	- **MAVLink signing** availability on the pinned firmware.
   415	- **Independent (out-of-companion-process) monitor** for H6(a): does not exist. The
   416	  correlated companion process-level fault — plausible-wrong `GPS_INPUT` with a falsified
   417	  integrity verdict — is **uncontrolled** pending such a monitor; no in-companion module is
   418	  independent of it.
   419	- **Content/innovation-liveness check** to fully close H4 against stale-but-advancing frames.
   420	- **Operational human-response control** for the unconscious-at-helm residual (H7): a second
